This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) because it proposes a proactive caching framework for mobile edge networks. It also uses deep learning algorithms to predict content demand, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses a distributed deep learning framework, which could place it in the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also deals with privacy concerns, which could place it in the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
